external_knowledge:
- "Olympic champions" refers to athletes who have participated in the Olympic Games;
- "collected a trove of medals" means winning multiple medals across different games and events;
- "three golden crowns" refers to three gold medals;
- "two silver badges" refers to two silver medals;
- "one bronze token" refers to one bronze medal;
- "shining brightly in the annals of their respective sports" emphasizes the significant achievements and recognition in their sports.

- 'Shone the brightest in the summer sun' is a metaphorical expression referring to athletes who have participated the most in the 'Summer' games;
- 'Top 3' refers to the athletes with the highest participation counts;
- 'Summer games' are a subset of the Olympic games held in the summer season.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(athlete_id) 
FROM participations
WHERE event_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT athlete_id) AS total_athletes_event_1
FROM participations
WHERE game_id = 1 AND event_id = 1;

SELECT DISTINCT a.name
FROM athletes a
JOIN participations p ON a.athlete_id = p.athlete_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'reaped the most glory' refers to the total number of medals won;
- 'grand arena of the Olympic Games' is a metaphorical expression for the Olympic Games;
- 'compare' refers to the additional metrics of average athlete age, number of athletes, and number of games participated in;
- 'top 10 countries' means the results are limited to the top 10 based on the total number of medals won.

- "seasoned" refers to athletes who are older than 25;
- "crossed the threshold of their mid-20s" refers to age > 25;
- "shown their prowess" refers to having participated in more than 2 events.
